rom parent state to a property containing optional","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child state.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"toWrappedState"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A case path from parent action to a case containing child actions."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"toWrappedAction"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that will be invoked with child actions against non-optional child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"state."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"wrapped"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The fileID.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"fileID"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The filePath.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"filePath"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The line."}]}],"name":"line"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The column."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"column"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"return-value","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Return Value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, if a parent feature holds onto a piece of optional child state, then it can","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"perform its core logic ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"text":" the child’s logic by using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  struct State {","    var child: Child.State?","    \/\/ ...","  }","  enum Action {","    case child(Child.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ifLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" operator does a number of things to try to enforce correctness:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It runs the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the parent feature to "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature would not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’d","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"out.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Automatically ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":"s out child state when an action is sent for alerts and confirmation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dialogs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Reducer\/ifLet(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-4ub6q"},{"type":"text","text":" for a more advanced operator suited"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to navigation."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Embeds a child reducer in a parent domain that works on an optional property of parent stat